events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Glasco Martin ran for three touchdowns, Lache Seastrunk had 185 yards rushing with an 80-yard score and Baylor again upset the BCS picture with a late-season victory, beating Kansas State (No. 1 BCS, No. 2 AP) 52-24 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Baylor blisters K-State, shakes BCS

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: Jordan Williamson hit a 37-yard field goal in overtime and No. 14 Stanford upset No. 1 Oregon 17-14, denying the Ducks a chance to clinch the Pac-12 North and derailing their straight shot at the BCS championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ducks' BCS hopes derailed with OT loss

events.name: Wake Forest Demon Deacons at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Third-ranked Notre Dame beat Wake Forest 38-0 Saturday to finish the season undefeated at home for the first time since 1998 and keep alive its national championship hopes.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 3 Irish crush Wake, now 11-0

events.name: Western Carolina Catamounts at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: Eddie Lacy rushed for three first-half touchdowns, AJ McCarron set Alabama's single-season record for passing TDs and the fourth-ranked Crimson Tide routed Western Carolina 49-0 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCarron sets Bama record

events.name: Georgia Southern Eagles at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Aaron Murray threw four touchdown passes, Todd Gurley became only the second true freshman in Georgia history to rush for 1,000 yards, and the No. 5 Bulldogs dropped FCS Georgia Southern 45-14 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: QBs star: Georgia's Murray

events.name: Jacksonville State Gamecocks at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Florida (No. 6 BCS, No. 7 AP) used a strong defensive effort to overcome a sluggish offensive performance in a 23-0 win over Jacksonville State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gators lean on D to hold off FCS foe

events.name: Ole Miss Rebels at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Jeremy Hill scored his third touchdown with 15 seconds left to lift LSU (No. 7 BCS, No. 8 AP) to a 41-35 victory over relentless but mistake-prone Mississippi on Saturday in a classic meeting between the rivals.
headlines.shortLinkText: LSU scores in final seconds to top Ole Miss

events.name: Sam Houston State Bearkats at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Johnny Manziel threw for 267 yards and three touchdowns, and ran for 100 yards and two more scores in a bit more than a half as Texas A&M beat Sam Houston State 47-28 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Manziel's big day keys Texas A&ampM's rout

events.name: Wofford Terriers at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Kenny Miles rushed for 127 yards and a touchdown and South Carolina (No. 9 BCS, No. 12 AP) pulled out a closer-than-expected 24-7 win over FCS opponent Wofford 24-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: S. Carolina puts away Wofford

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: Devonta Freeman ran for 148 yards and two touchdowns, Florida State's top-ranked defense lived up to its billing and the No. 10 Seminoles rolled past Maryland 41-14 Saturday to earn a spot in the Atlantic Coast Conference championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fla. St. in ACC title game

events.name: NC State Wolfpack at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd threw for five touchdowns and ran for three more scores to lead No. 11 Clemson to a record-shattering 62-48 win over North Carolina State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boyd accounts for 8 TDs in Clemson's laugher

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Landry Jones threw six touchdown passes, including a 5-yarder to Kenny Stills with 24 seconds left, to lift Oklahoma to a wild 50-49 win over West Virginia on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sooners deal WVU 5th straight loss

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Taylor Martinez threw for 308 yards and two touchdowns to Kenny Bell while becoming Nebraska's all-time passing leader in a 38-14 victory over Minnesota on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Martinez new passing leader as Nebraska rolls

events.name: California Golden Bears at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: Sean Mannion passed for 325 yards and four touchdowns, and Oregon State (No. 16 BCS, No. 15 AP) routed California 62-14 on Saturday night in what could be Jeff Tedford's final game as the Golden Bears' coach.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mannion tosses 4 TDs as Oregon St. pastes Cal

events.name: USC Trojans at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Brett Hundley passed for 234 yards and a touchdown and rushed for two more scores as No. 17 UCLA beat USC (No. 18 BCS, No. 21 AP) 38-28, clinching the Pac-12 South title and emphatically snapping a five-game losing streak in their crosstown rivalry.
headlines.shortLinkText: UCLA wins as Barkley hurt

events.name: Utah State Aggies at Louisiana Tech Bulldogs

headlines.description: Chuckie Keeton threw for 340 yards and two touchdowns, rushed for 121 yards and two touchdowns, and Utah State beat Louisiana Tech (No. 20 BCS, No. 19 AP) 48-41 in overtime on Saturday after letting a 24-point lead slip away.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah St. wins in OT, clinches share of WAC

events.name: Iowa Hawkeyes at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Devin Gardner accounted for six touchdowns to help Michigan (No. 21 BCS, No. 23 AP) rout Iowa 42-17 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Toussaint hurt; Robinson at RB

events.name: Rutgers Scarlet Knights at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: Savon Huggins ran for a career-high 179 yards, and Rutgers' defense had another shut-down showing Saturday in a 10-3 victory over Cincinnati that kept the 22nd-ranked Scarlet Knights in control of the Big East.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rutgers tops Cincy, holds control of Big East

events.name: Texas Tech Red Raiders at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: Isaiah Anderson had a career-best 174 yards receiving and caught three long touchdown passes from Clint Chelf in his final home game, leading Oklahoma State (No. 24 BCS) to a 59-21 win against No. 23 Texas Tech on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anderson key as OK State thumps Texas Tech

events.name: Washington Huskies at Colorado Buffaloes

headlines.description: Keith Price threw a career-best five touchdown passes and Washington (No. 25 BCS) overcame a slow start to whip hapless Colorado 38-3 on Saturday for the Huskies' fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Price throws 5 TDs as Washington rips Colorado

events.name: Northwestern Wildcats at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Jeff Budzien kicked a 27-yard field goal with 7:30 remaining, and Northwestern was able to hold on to this fourth-quarter lead, beating Michigan State 23-20 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: N'western takes lead in 4th, holds off Mich. St.

events.name: Kent State Golden Flashes at Bowling Green Falcons

headlines.description: Dri Archer ran for 241 yards and two long touchdowns to lead Kent State (No. 25 AP) to its first Mid-American Conference title game with a 31-24 victory over Bowling Green on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kent State clinches berth in first MAC title game

headlines.description: Tulsa 23, UCF 21
headlines.shortLinkText: Tulsa 23, UCF 21

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: Receiver Allen Robinson had three highlight-reel scoring catches and Matt McGloin threw for four touchdowns to lead Penn State in a 45-22 win Saturday over Indiana.
headlines.shortLinkText: Penn State LB Mauti injured in rout

headlines.description: Marshall 44, Houston 41
headlines.shortLinkText: Marshall 44, Houston 41

events.name: Temple Owls at Army Black Knights

headlines.description: Montel Harris rushed for a career-high and Big East-record 351 yards and seven touchdowns, Matt Brown scored twice before leaving the game with an injury, and Temple beat Army 63-32 on Saturday for its fifth straight win in the series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris piles up 351 yards, 7 TDs as Temple rolls

events.name: Temple Owls at Army Black Knights
Arkansas Razorbacks at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Tyler Russell threw for 274 yards and four touchdowns to lead Mississippi State to a 45-14 victory over Arkansas on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell tosses 4 TDs, Miss. St. routs Arkansas

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at Boston College Eagles

headlines.description: Logan Thomas threw for two touchdowns -- the second a 7-yarder to Randall Dunn in overtime -- and ran for another score to help Virginia Tech keep its bowl hopes alive with a 30-23 comeback win over Boston College on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Va. Tech defeats Boston College in OT

headlines.description: Tre Mason threw for two touchdowns and Onterio McCalebb added two rushing scores to lead Auburn to a 51-7 win over Alabama A&M on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mason, Auburn have way with Alabama A&M

events.name: Washington State Cougars at Arizona State Sun Devils

headlines.description: Quarterbacks Taylor Kelly and Michael Eubank accounted for six touchdowns Saturday, and Arizona State became bowl eligible with a 46-7 rout over Washington State that ended the Sun Devils' four-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arizona State cruises, becomes bowl eligible

events.name: South Florida Bulls at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: Stephen Morris threw for 413 yards and three scores, Herb Waters had an 87-yard touchdown catch for Miami's longest reception in more than five years and the Hurricanes rolled past South Florida 40-9 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morris throws for 413 yards as Miami cruises

Duke Blue Devils at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Tevin Washington passed for three touchdowns and ran for another score to lead Georgia Tech to a 42-24 win over Duke on Saturday, preserving the Yellow Jackets' hopes of playing in the Atlantic Coast Conference championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ga. Tech stops Duke, moves atop ACC Coastal

events.name: Colorado State Rams at Boise State Broncos

headlines.description: Boise State scored on its first offensive play Saturday and never looked back in a 42-14 victory over Colorado State.

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: Carlos Hyde scored on a 2-yard run in overtime Saturday, giving Ohio State a 21-14 victory over Wisconsin and keeping the Buckeyes' hopes of a perfect season alive.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ohio St. bests Wisconsin in OT to stay perfect

Syracuse Orange at Missouri Tigers

headlines.description: Ryan Nassib threw a 17-yard touchdown pass to a wide-open Alec Lemon with 20 seconds to go, capping a 21-point fourth quarter as Syracuse spoiled Missouri's home finale with a 31-27 victory on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Syracuse rallies past Missouri in 4th quarter

events.name: Tennessee Volunteers at Vanderbilt Commodores

headlines.description: Andre Hal intercepted two passes and Jordan Rodgers threw for two touchdowns as Vanderbilt routed Tennessee 41-18 Saturday night for the Commodores' fifth straight victory, clinching their first winning record in the regular season since 1982.

headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa St. cruises as QB Richardson breaks out

events.name: Samford Bulldogs at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Freshman Jalen Whitlow passed for one touchdown and ran for another, Raymond Sanders rushed for a career-high 123 yards and a TD and Kentucky blew out Samford 34-3 Saturday night to end an eight-game losing streak.
